---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - The Null Hypothesis"
  description="Front-end engineer with 13 years of experience building for the web"
>
  <article>
    <header class="post-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm Kumak, a front-end developer who's been writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for 13 years.
        I have a passion for simple things that just work.
      </p>

      <h2>Why "The Null Hypothesis"</h2>
      <p>
        In statistics, you start with no assumptions and see what the data tells you.
        That's how I approach things. No preconceived notions about what should work.
        Just what actually does.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Care About</h2>
      <p>
        Web standards, accessibility, and semantic HTML. I follow the newest trends, but prefer to
        be one step behind when implementing them.
      </p>

      <p>
        I believe in <strong>simplicity over complexity</strong>. Elegant solutions over clever hacks.
        Systems that grow gracefully rather than collapse under their own weight.
      </p>

      <h2>Side Projects</h2>
      <p>
        In my spare time, I write CLI tools for AI agents. Current project:
        <a href="https://github.com/szymdzum/browser-debugger-cli">browser-debugger-cli</a>,
        a tool for browser debugging via Chrome DevTools Protocol.
      </p>

      <h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
      <p>
        Front-end development, developer tooling, and working with AI agents.
        Practical patterns over theory. Things I've tested and found useful.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .post-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: calc(var(--space-xs) * 0.5);
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .post-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-tighter);
    word-spacing: var(--word-spacing-tight);
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .post-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
